Yes, multiple effective rotavirus vaccines are available worldwide, including monovalent and pentavalent options that have significantly reduced cases of severe illness and deaths since their introduction in 2006. Despite limitations such as cold chain requirements and variable effectiveness in resource-limited areas, these vaccines remain clinically proven and recommended by global health organizations.

\boxed{A}

The summary focuses only on the core clinical facts regarding availability, types, impact, and real-world implementation of rotavirus vaccination — omitting logistical or socioeconomic details not directly tied to medical validity or public health utility. It clearly affirms existence and efficacy without overreaching into unverified claims about performance across all populations.

